## Threat Model

<!--
Default threat model: standard web-server.
- Attacker has unauthenticated HTTP access (can send any request)
- If auth exists, attacker also has a valid low-privilege account
- Network position: internet
- Not assumed: local code execution, side-channel attacks, DoS

Override for your repo:

- This repo is an internal-only CLI binary — threat model is "hostile input files" not "network attacker"
- This repo handles PCI data — elevate all logging of request bodies to P0
- This repo is a public OSS library — threat model includes a malicious caller of every public API
-->

## Verification Bar

<!--
Default: every behavior claim in a finding must include a file:line citation with verbatim quote.

Stricter options:

- Behavior claims must cite both the alleged bug site AND the alleged call path that reaches it
- Security findings require a concrete exploit payload (not "could be injectable")
- Architectural findings require a proposed fix that compiles
-->

## Repo-Specific Known Patterns

<!--
LOAD-BEARING SECTION: The design-decision classifier reads this to decide whether a finding
is `actionable` (blocks merge) or `design_decision` (disclosed but does not block).

Document patterns that look wrong but are intentional in this repo. Be specific — include file
path, the pattern name, and the reasoning. The classifier quotes your entry verbatim as evidence
when it marks a related finding as `design_decision`.

Format tip: each bullet should contain (a) the file or glob, (b) what the pattern is, (c) why
it is intentional. A reviewer unfamiliar with the repo must be able to read your entry and
understand that this is deliberate, not debt.

Examples:

- `app/auth/dev_login.py` — password-less login endpoint is gated by `ENV === 'development'`
  and documented in README as a test-only helper. It is NOT shipped to production. Do not flag
  missing auth on this file.
- `src/observer/ring_buffer.rs` — the unsafe pointer arithmetic in `push_back` has a full
  `// SAFETY:` comment and was independently audited (see ADR-0007). Do not re-flag the unsafe
  block unless the preconditions change.
- `packages/legacy/*` — this directory is frozen and scheduled for removal in Q3. Do not flag
  pre-existing issues here even if the formatter touched the file.
- `src/**/**.generated.ts` — code generation output. Do not flag style or naming.
- In `services/billing/`, all functions return `Result<T, BillingError>` and the single `.unwrap()`
  in `BillingClient::new()` is acceptable because startup failure MUST panic (see CLAUDE.md §
  Billing Guarantees).

If a P2 nit is reported that you believe is "just style, it's fine" — STOP and decide: either
fix it, or add it here with a real reason. The pipeline no longer lets P2 pass silently.
-->

